{"title_page": "Guy Williams (rugby league)", "text_new": "{{Use dmy dates|date=July 2013}}\n{{Use Australian English|date=July 2013}}\n{{Infobox rugby league biography\n|name     = Guy Williams\n|fullname       = Guy Williams\n|nickname       = \n|image          = Guy Williams.jpg\n|image_size     = \n|position       = {{rlp|SR}}, [[Rugby league positions#Backs|Utility back]]\n|birth_date     = {{birth date and age|df=yes|1984|4|28}}\n|birth_place    = \n|height         = {{convert|185|cm|ftin|abbr=on}}\n|weight         = {{convert|95|kg|stlb|abbr=on}}\n|currentclub    = {{leagueicon|Brisbane Broncos|16}} [[Brisbane Broncos]]\n|clubnumber     = \n|club1          = [[Brisbane Broncos]]\n|year1start     = 2009\n|year1end       = \n|appearances1   = 5\n|tries1         = 0\n|goals1         = 0\n|fieldgoals1    = 0\n|points1        = 0\n|club2          = [[Central Comets]]\n|year2start     = 2009\n|year2end       = 11\n|club3          = [[Toulouse Olympique]]\n|year3start     = 2011\n|year3end       = 13\n|appearances3   = 37\n|tries3         = 8\n|goals3         = 0\n|fieldgoals3    = 0\n|points3        = 32\n|club4          = {{nowrap|[[Central Queensland Capras]]}}\n|year4start     = 2013\n|year4end       = 15\n|club5          = [[L\u00e9zignan Sangliers]]\n|year5start     = 2015\n|year5end       = 16\n|appearances5   = 18\n|tries5         = 5\n|goals5         = 0\n|fieldgoals5    = 0\n|points5        = 20\n|updated        = 1 February 2019\n|source         = <ref>[http://www.rugbyleagueproject.org/players/Guy_Williams/summary.html Rugby League Project]</ref><ref>[http://www.itsrugby.co.uk/player_16487.html itsrugby]</ref>\n|new            = yes\n}}\n\n'''Guy Williams''' (born 28 April 1984), is an Australian former professional [[rugby league]] footballer who last played for the [[L\u00e9zignan Sangliers]] in the [[Elite One Championship]] and previously the [[Brisbane Broncos]] in the [[NRL]] competition. He played as a [[Rugby league positions#Backs|utility back]] or in the [[Rugby league positions#The back row|second row]].\n\n==Playing career==\nWilliams made his first grade debut for Brisbane in Round 15 2009 against Cronulla which ended in a 46-12 loss.  Williams went on to play for the [[Central Comets]] in the [[Queensland Cup]].<ref name=\"Williams eyes off an NRL start at broncos\">{{cite web|url=http://www.themorningbulletin.com.au/story/2009/01/07/williams-eyes-off-an-nrl-start-at-broncos|title=Williams eyes off an NRL start at broncos|publisher=The Morning Bulletin|date=7 January 2009|accessdate=3 July 2018}}</ref> \n\nIn 2011, Williams left [[Central Comets]] and moved to France where he captained [[Toulouse Olympique]]. In 2013 he returned to [[Central Comets]] now renamed [[Central Queensland Capras]] and went on to captain the side as well as play for them in over 150 games in his two spells. \n\n==Post playing==\nWilliams previously worked at The Morning Bulletin in Rockhampton as a sports journalist.\n\n==References==\n{{reflist}}\n\n==External links==\n*[https://web.archive.org/web/20090912013742/http://www.broncos.com.au/default.aspx?s=player-profile-display&id=1645&team=Broncos&guy-williams Brisbane Broncos profile]\n*[https://web.archive.org/web/20091003041521/http://comets.com.au/this-season/player-list/guy-williams/ Central Comets profile]\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Williams, Guy}}\n[[Category:Australian rugby league players]]\n[[Category:1984 births]]\n[[Category:Brisbane Broncos players]]\n[[Category:Rugby league centres]]\n[[Category:Rugby league five-eighths]]\n[[Category:Toulouse Olympique players]]\n[[Category:Rugby league locks]]\n[[Category:Central Queensland Capras players]]\n[[Category:Rugby league second-rows]]\n[[Category:Australian journalists]]\n[[Category:Living people]]\n[[Category:Place of birth missing (living people)]]\n", "text_old": "{{Use dmy dates|date=July 2013}}\n{{Use Australian English|date=July 2013}}\n{{Infobox rugby league biography\n|name     = Guy Williams\n|fullname       = Guy W