ess. 1998. {{ISBN|9780674445796}}\n\n==== Anthology ====\n\n*''Last Days at Hot Slit: The Radical Feminism of Andrea Dworkin'', Fateman, Joanna; Scholder, Amy, eds. Cambridge: The MIT Press. 2019. {{ISBN|9781635900804}}\n\n==== Chapters in other anthologies ====\n\n* {{Cite book | last =  | first =  | contribution = Pornography happens to women | editor-last1 = Lederer | editor-first1 = Laura | editor-last2 = Delgado | editor-first2 = Richard | editor-link1 = Laura Lederer | editor-link2 = Richard Delgado | title = The price we pay: the case against racist speech, hate propaganda, and pornography | pages = | publisher = Hill and Wang | location = New York | year = 1995 | isbn = 978-0809015771 | ref = }}\n* [[Diane Bell|Bell, Diane]], & [[Renate Klein]], eds. (1996). \"''Dworkin on Dworkin''\". ''Radically Speaking: Feminism Reclaimed'' ([[North Melbourne, Victoria|N. Melbourne, Vic., Australia]]: Spinifex. pp 203-0217. {{ISBN|1-875559-38-8}}.<ref name=\":4\" />\n* {{cite book | last =  | first =  | contribution = Biological superiority: the world's most dangerous and deadly idea | editor-last1 = Jackson | editor-first1 = Stevi | editor-last2 = Scott | editor-first2 = Sue | editor-link1 = Stevi Jackson | editor-link2 = Sue Scott (sociologist) | title = Feminism and sexuality: a reader | pages = 57\u201361 | publisher = Columbia University Press | location = New York | year = 1996 | isbn = 978-0231107082 | ref =  }}\n* {{cite book | last =  | first =  | contribution = Pornography | editor-last1 = Jackson | editor-first1 = Stevi | editor-last2 = Scott | editor-first2 = Sue | editor-link1 = Stevi Jackson | editor-link2 = Sue Scott (sociologist) | title = Feminism and sexuality: a reader | pages = 297\u2013299 | publisher = Columbia University Press | location = New York | year = 1996 | isbn = 978-0231107082 | ref =  }}\n* {{cite book|last=|first=|contribution=Landscape of the ordinary: violence against women|editor-last=Morgan|editor-first=Robin|editor-link=Robin Morgan|title=Sisterhood is forever: the women's anthology for a new millennium|pages=[https://archive.org/details/sisterhoodisfore00morg/page/58 58\u201369]|publisher=Washington Square Press|location=New York|year=2003|isbn=978-0743466271|title-link=Sisterhood Is Forever: The Women's Anthology for a New Millennium}}<ref name=\"illinois1\">{{Cite book|url=https://archive.org/details/sisterhoodisfore00morg|title=Library Resource Finder: Table of Contents for: Sisterhood is forever: the women's anthology for a new millennium|website=vufind.carli.illinois.edu|publisher=[[DePaul University]]|year=2003|isbn=978-0743466271|accessdate=October 15, 2015}}\n\n*{{Cite book | last = Dworkin | first = Andrea | contribution = Pornography, prostitution and a beautiful and tragic recent history | editor-last1 = Whisnant | editor-first1 = Rebecca | editor-last2 = Stark | editor-first2 = Christine | editor-link1 = Rebecca Whisnant | title = Not for sale: feminists resisting prostitution and pornography | pages = 137\u2013158 | publisher = Spinifex Press | location = North Melbourne, Victoria | year = 2004 | isbn = 978-1876756499 }}</ref>\n\n=== Fiction ===\n\n*{{cite book|last=|first=|title=the new womans broken heart: short stories|publisher=Frog in the Well|location=East Palo Alto, CA|pages=|year=1980|isbn=978-0960362806}}\n* {{cite book|last=|first=|title=Ice and fire: a novel|publisher=Secker & Warburg|location=London|pages=|year=1986|isbn=978-0436139604|url-access=registration|url=https://archive.org/details/icefirenovel0000dwor}}\n* {{cite book|last=|first=|title=Mercy|publisher=Four Walls Eight Windows|location=New York|pages=|year=1991|isbn=978-0941423694|url-access=registration|url=https://archive.org/details/mercy00andr}}\n\n=== Poetry ===\n\n*{{cite book|last=|first=|title=Child|publisher=Heraklion|location=Crete|pages=|year=1966|isbn=|oclc=4708955}}\n*{{cite book|last=|first=|title=Morning hair|publisher=Philadelphia College of Art|location=Philadelphia|pages=|year=1967|isbn=|oclc=9290267}}\n\n=== Articles ===\n* {{cite book|last=|first=|title=Marx and Gandhi were liberals: feminism and the \"radical\" left|publisher=Frog in the Well|isbn=|location=East Palo Alto, CA|pages=|date=1977|oclc=6189987}}\n* {{cite book|last=|first=|title=Why so-called radical men love and need pornography|publisher=Frog in the Well|isbn=|location=East Palo Alto, CA|pages=|date=1978|oclc=8309555}}\n* {{cite journal|last=|first=|title=Against the male flood: censorship, pornography, and equality|journal=Harvard Journal of Law & Gender|volume=8|pages=1\u201330|date=Spring 1985|url=http://heinonline.org/HOL/LandingPage?handle=hein.journals/mjgl1&div=5&id=&page=|ref=|via=}} [http://pzacad.pitzer.edu/~mma/teaching/MS110/reading/feminism&pornography_pp19-38_94-120.pdf Pdf]\n* {{cite book|last=|first=|title=Pornography is a Civil Rights Issue for Women|year=1986|isbn=|publisher=Organizing Against Pornography|location=Minneapolis, MN|pages=|oclc=18843030}} [https://web.archive.org/web/20030402193857/http://www.isiswomen.org/wia/wia398/vaw00006.html Page 1 of 4] [http://www.nostatusquo.com/ACLU/dworkin/WarZoneChaptIVF2.html Page 2 of 4.] [https://web.archive.org/web/20030402193857/http://www.isiswomen.org/wia/wia398/vaw00006.html Page 3 of 4] [http://www.nostatusquo.com/ACLU/dworkin/WarZoneChaptIVF4.html Page 4 of 4]\n* {{Cite news|last=|first=|url=|title=Pornography is a civil rights issue for women|work=[[No Status Quo|NoStatusQuo]]|access-date=|url-status=live|publisher=[[Nikki Craft]]|date=1986}} [https://web.archive.org/web/20160304090525/http://www.michelepolak.com/WMST100fall10/Weekly_Schedule_files/dworkin_porn.pdf Pdf.] [https://web.archive.org/web/20030402193857/http://www.isiswomen.org/wia/wia398/vaw00006.html Page 1 of 2] [http://www.nostatusquo.com/ACLU/dworkin/WarZoneChaptIVF2.html Page 2 of 2]\n* {{cite journal|last=|first=|title=The ACLU: bait and switch|journal=[[Yale Journal of Law and Feminism]]|volume=1|issue=1|pages=37\u201340|date=Spring 1989|url=http://heinonline.org/HOL/LandingPage?handle=hein.journals/yjfem1&div=8&id=&page=|ref=|via=}} [http://digitalcommons.law.yale.edu/cgi/viewcontent.cgi?article=1005&context=yjlf Pdf]\n* {{cite journal|last=|first=|title=Prostitution and male supremacy|journal=Michigan Journal of Gender and Law|volume=1|pages=1\u201312|date=1993|url=http://heinonline.org/HOL/LandingPage?handle=hein.journals/mjgl1&div=5&id=&page=|ref=|via=}} [http://www.nostatusquo.com/ACLU/dworkin/MichLawJourI.html Page 1 of 2.] [http://www.nostatusquo.com/ACLU/dworkin/MichLawJourII.html Page 2 of 2]\n* {{cite book|last=|first=|title=Are you listening, Hillary? President Rape is who he is|url=http://andreadworkin.com/hillary/index.html|publisher=|year=1999|isbn=|location=|pages=}}\n* Excerpt with ''Note from John Stoltenberg, May 25, 2007''\n* {{cite journal|last=|first=|title=Book review: A good rape|url=http://www.newstatesman.com/node/157952|journal=[[New Statesman]]|volume=|pages=|via=|date=June 30, 2003}}\n* Review of ''Lucky'' by Alice Sebold, {{ISBN|978-0684857824}}\n* {{cite journal|last=|first=|date=September 22, 2003|title=Book review: Out of the closet|url=http://www.newstatesman.com/node/158370|journal=[[New Statesman]]|volume=|pages=|via=}}\n* Review of ''Normal: transsexual CEOs, cross-dressing cops, and hermaphrodites with attitude'' by Amy Bloom, {{ISBN|978-0679456520}}\n* {{cite journal|last=|first=|title=The day I was drugged and raped|url=http://www.newstatesman.com/comment/2013/03/day-i-was-drugged-and-raped|journal=[[New Statesman]]|volume=|pages=|via=|date=March 4, 2013}}\n\n=== Speeches ===\n\n*[https://web.archive.org/web/20030402193857/http://www.isiswomen.org/wia/wia398/vaw00006.html Why Men Like Pornography & Prostitution So Much] Andrea Dworkin Keynote Speech at International Trafficking Conference, 1989. ''(Audio File: 22 min, 128&nbsp;kbit/s, mp3)''\n*[http://andreadworkin.com/audio/attgeneralcommNYC_M.mp3 Andrea Dworkin's Attorney General's Commission Testimony] on Pornograp